it.emarolab.owloop.core

Interface DataProperty.Domain<O,J,Y>

  • Type Parameters:
    O - the type of ontology in which the axioms for classes will be applied.
    J - the type of the described class.
    Y - the type of restriction for the EntitySet managed by this Descriptor.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Axiom, Axiom.Descriptor<O,J>, DataProperty<O,J>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataPropertyExpression.Domain
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DomainRangeDataPropertyDesc, FullDataPropertyDesc
    Enclosing interface:
    DataProperty<O,J>

    public static interface DataProperty.Domain<O,J,Y>
extends DataProperty<O,J>
    Implementation of this interface enables a DataProperty to have the DataProperty.Domain expression.

    This descriptor synchronises the definition of the domain of the grounded data property. Definition is defined as a conjunction of restriction properties that create a super class of the described ontological class. The restriction can be of the following types:

    • class restriction: a domain is restricted to a class.
    • data restriction: a domain is defined to have data properties into a given range. It is also possible to describe the cardinality of this restriction to be: existential (some), universal (all), minimal, maximal and exact.
    • object restriction: a domain is defined to have data properties into a given class. It is also possible to describe the cardinality of this restriction to be: existential (some), universal (all), minimal, maximal and exact.
    If this expression is used, it is not possible to use the build() operation since the restrictions are not simple OWL entities like OWLClass, OWLIndividual, OWLObjectProperty and OWLDataProperty.

        This method is used to update specific Axiom.EntitySet (or Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet) by synchronizing the internal state of the descriptor with the queried OWL structure, such that they are equal. It is based on EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet).
